<subSubSection id="C35CACEA7C19CA74FF13FB5B229DFAE6" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF9FF617C19CA74FF13FB5B229DFAE6" blockId="14.[163,780,1263,1346]" pageId="14" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis id="B93223737C19CA74FF13FB5B210EFAA0" box="[163,360,1263,1284]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="234">Species included:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C4684E27C19CA74FEC6FB5B2363FAA0" authority="Zweifel, 1972" authorityName="Zweifel" authorityYear="1972" box="[374,773,1263,1285]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Lobulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brongersmai">
<emphasis id="B93223737C19CA74FEC6FB5B2200FAA0" box="[374,614,1263,1284]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="234">Lobulia brongersmai</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD782907C19CA74FDDCFB5B2363FAA0" author="Zweifel RG" box="[620,773,1263,1285]" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" pagination="530 - 539" refId="ref46955" refString="Zweifel RG. 1972. A new scincid lizard of the genus Leiolopisma from New Guinea. Zoologische Mededelingen 47: 530 - 539." type="journal article" year="1972">Zweifel, 1972</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C4684E27C19CA74FF13FAB92259FA87" authority="(Boulenger, 1897)" baseAuthorityName="Boulenger" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[163,575,1293,1315]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Lobulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="B93223737C19CA74FF13FAB92107FA86" box="[163,353,1293,1314]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="234">Lobulia elegans</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD782907C19CA74FEC3FAB92252FA86" author="Boulenger GA" box="[371,564,1293,1315]" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" pagination="6 - 13" refId="ref43763" refString="Boulenger GA. 1897. Descriptions of new lizards and frogs from Mount Victoria, Owen Stanley Range, New Guinea, collected by Mr. A. S. Anthony. Annals and Magazine of Natural History Series 6 19: 6 - 13." type="journal article" year="1897">Boulenger, 1897</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C4684E27C19CA74FDFDFAB9210BFAE5" authority="(Loveridge, 1945)" baseAuthorityName="Loveridge" baseAuthorityYear="1945" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Lobulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lobulus">
<emphasis id="B93223737C19CA74FDFDFAB9236DFA86" box="[589,779,1293,1314]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="234">Lobulia lobulus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD782907C19CA74FF1BFA982102FAE6" author="Loveridge A" box="[171,356,1324,1346]" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" pagination="47 - 52" refId="ref45207" refString="Loveridge A. 1945. New scincid lizards of the genera Tropidophorus and Lygosoma from New Guinea. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 58: 47 - 52." type="journal article" year="1945">Loveridge, 1945</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; and new species described below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35CACEA7C19CA74FF13FADF21F8F975" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BF9FF617C19CA74FF13FADF21F8F975" blockId="14.[163,781,1387,1745]" pageId="14" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis id="B93223737C19CA74FF13FADF2126FA24" box="[163,320,1387,1408]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="234">Distribution:</emphasis>
Members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4684E27C19CA74FE57FADF2223FA24" authorityName="Greer" authorityYear="1974" box="[487,581,1387,1408]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Lobulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93223737C19CA74FE57FADF2223FA24" box="[487,581,1387,1408]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="234">Lobulia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are widespread along most of the montane regions of New 
<collectingCountry id="F351BFF17C19CA74FD1DFA3D2363FA3B" box="[685,773,1417,1439]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="14" pageNumber="234">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, ranging from the central Owen Stanley Mountains in the Papuan Peninsula in the east (
<taxonomicName id="4C4684E27C19CA74FDD2FA732285FA78" baseAuthorityName="Boulenger" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[610,739,1479,1500]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Lobulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="B93223737C19CA74FDD2FA732285FA78" box="[610,739,1479,1500]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="234">Lo. elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) to the Arfak Mountains in the Vogelkop Peninsula in the west. Most species are montane, found at elevations up to 
<quantity id="4CBE52847C19CA74FF70F9972170F99C" box="[192,278,1571,1592]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" unit="m" value="2700.0">2700 m</quantity>
a.s.l.; however, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4684E27C19CA74FE7DF99722E1F99C" authorityName="Zweifel" authorityYear="1972" box="[461,647,1571,1592]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Lobulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brongersmai">
<emphasis id="B93223737C19CA74FE7DF99722E1F99C" box="[461,647,1571,1592]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="234">Lo. brongersmai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in the lowlands and hill regions of the northern versant of New 
<collectingCountry id="F351BFF17C19CA74FF49F9D4212AF9D2" box="[249,332,1632,1654]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="14" pageNumber="234">Guinea</collectingCountry>
(
<quantity id="4CBE52847C19CA74FEEBF9D421ADF9D1" box="[347,459,1632,1653]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" metricValueMax="13.4" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" unit="m" value="670.0" valueMax="1340.0" valueMin="0.0">0–1340 m</quantity>
a.s.l.). 
<taxonomicName id="4C4684E27C19CA74FDADF9D4236CF9D1" authorityName="Zweifel" authorityYear="1972" box="[541,778,1632,1653]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Lobulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brongersmai">
<emphasis id="B93223737C19CA74FDADF9D4236CF9D1" box="[541,778,1632,1653]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="234">Lobulia brongersmai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only member of the genus to be found below elevations of 
<quantity id="4CBE52847C19CA74FE87F9292118F917" box="[311,382,1693,1715]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" unit="m" value="700.0">700 m</quantity>
, the lowest recorded locality for 
<taxonomicName id="4C4684E27C19CA74FD59F92A21FFF975" authority="(Kraus, 2020)" baseAuthorityName="Kraus" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Lobulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="B93223737C19CA74FD59F92A2091F975" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="234">Lo. elegans</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD782907C19CA74FEB5F90821E9F975" author="Kraus F" box="[261,399,1724,1745]" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" pagination="201 - 214" refId="ref45028" refString="Kraus F. 2020. A new species of Lobulia (Squamata: Scincidae) from Papua New Guinea. Zootaxa 4779: 201 - 214." type="journal article" year="2020">Kraus, 2020</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35CACEA7C19CA74FF13F94E242AFA3A" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF9FF617C19CA74FF13F94E242AFA3A" blockId="14.[163,778,1786,1900]" lastBlockId="14.[827,1443,1262,1438]" pageId="14" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis id="B93223737C19CA74FF13F94E2177F8AB" box="[163,273,1786,1807]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="234">Remarks:</emphasis>
Molecular evidence suggests that at least two other species not already named or described herein occur in the genus: one in Woitape (BPBM 18689–90; WGS 84: 
<geoCoordinate id="EE7299A67C19CA74FE23F8E22189F8C8" box="[403,495,1878,1900]" degrees="8.545" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" precision="55" value="-8.545">8.545°S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE7299A67C19CA74FE4CF8E22210F8C8" box="[508,630,1878,1900]" degrees="147.251" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" precision="55" value="147.251">147.251°E</geoCoordinate>
) and one on Mt Yakapi in the Muller Range (BPBM 34161; WGS 84: 
<geoCoordinate id="EE7299A67C19CA74FCDAFAB923ACFA87" box="[874,970,1293,1315]" degrees="5.666" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" precision="55" value="-5.666">5.666°S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE7299A67C19CA74FC6AFAB9243AFA87" box="[986,1116,1293,1315]" degrees="142.643" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="14" pageNumber="234" precision="55" value="142.643">142.643°E</geoCoordinate>
). However, since both are only known from a few specimens each, and are not extremely morphologically distinct, we refrain from formally describing them until further material can be collected and examined.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
